Statements Issued on 60th Birthday of DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 7 (KCNA) -- An Indian and Syrian figures issued statements on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Harising Khang, member of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of India (Marxist), in his statement issued on Aug. 28 said that the 60-year-long history of the DPRK represents that of struggle to creditably safeguard the sovereignty of the country and dignity of the nation while frustrating the imperialists' moves for aggression and meeting their challenge, and to realize independence in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliance in national defence and build a socialist state centered on the popular masses.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He referred to the fact that President Kim Il Sung developed the DPRK into one representing the independent right of the working people and organizing their creative abilities after indicating unique ideas and theories on nation-building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 General Secretary Kim Jong Il is demonstrating the dignity and might of the DPRK with Songun politics, he stressed, adding that thanks to his Songun leadership, rosy is the future of the Republic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saber Ballul, head of Department of the Political Faculty of University of Damascus of Syria, in his statement on Aug. 30 noted that the foundation of the DPRK meant the birth of a genuine people's country for the first time in Korea with long history and brilliant culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that the DPRK will demonstrate its dignity as a powerful country as it is led by Kim Jong Il who is always leading the country to victory and glory, carrying forward the cause of the President.

Lots of Exhibitions and Shows Introducing Songun Korea Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 7 (KCNA) -- Korean book, photo, art and handicraft exhibitions and Kimjongilia shows introducing Songun Korea were held in more than 40 countries over 150 times on several occasions during 8 months this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They helped a lot of progressive people of the world to know better about socialist Korea which is strikingly demonstrating the dignity and honor of the country and nation to the whole world under the leadership of the peerlessly great persons, and express support and solidarity with it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Political parties, organizations and individual figures of various countries sponsored with sincerity the exhibitions to give wide publicity to the just cause of the Korean people on important occasions including the Day of the Sun, the February holiday and the army day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prominent figures of several countries and regions including Dalian of China, Moscow of Russia, Italy, the national museum of Lithuania and Lima of Peru said that they were happy to hear the news about the opening of Korean book, photo and art exhibitions, expressing their willingness to learn more about man-centered socialist Korea through them and boost friendly and cooperative relations among countries.

DPRK Birthday Marked in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 6 (KCNA) -- Seminars were held in Italy, Bangladesh, Mexico, Romania and Bulgaria and a friendly meeting, a book and photo exhibition, a film show and an art performance took place in Laos between August 28 and 30 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venues of the functions were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il, photos showing their glorious revolutionary history and undying feats and books and photos dealing with the 60-year-long history of the DPRK recorded with victory and glory under the wise leadership of the peerlessly great men and the Korean people's struggle for building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pasquale Felice, representative of the Firenze Branch of the Unified Communist Party of Italy, in his speech praised the President who, after embarking upon the road of revolution in his teens, not only achieved the historical cause of national liberation by making long journeys of bloody battles against the robber-like Japanese imperialists but also founded the DPRK and turned it into a socialist power, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defense. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chief of the Bulgarian Group for the Study of the Juche Idea in his speech made at the seminar referred to the painstaking efforts exerted by the President to prevent the territorial division imposed by foreign forces upon Korea and establish a unified government representing the whole of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Romania-Korea Friendship Association in his speech said that Songun politics serves as an all-powerful treasured sword firmly guaranteeing the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation as the main political mode of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers including M. Jahangir Khan, advisor of the Bangladesh Barisal Society for the Study of Songun Policy, stressed that developing countries including Bangladesh should achieve their stability and progress by learning from the Songun politics of the DPRK, noting that the secret of the invincibility of the DPRK lies in the Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar held in Bulgaria.

