Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Brazil
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 7 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il's famous work "The Juche Philosophy Is an Original Revolutionary Philosophy" was brought out in booklet by a publishing house of Brazil on August 30. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on July 26, Juche 85 (1996), makes a scientific analysis into the limitation of the time the preceding philosophy was enunciated and the originality of the Juche philosophy. It also deals with the idea that the Juche philosophy serves as the revolutionary philosophy and political philosophy of the Workers' Party of Korea and principled matters arising in the study, explanation and dissemination of the Juche philosophy.

60th Birthday of DPRK Celebrated Abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 7 (KCNA) -- A meeting and film show were held in Russia on Sept. 3 and meetings, seminars, round-table talks, photo exhibitions and film shows in Pakistan, Mexico and Britain in the period from Aug. 26 to 29 on the occasion of the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venues of the photo exhibitions were photos showing the glorious 60-year-long history covered by the DPRK under the wise leadership of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK Vladimir Tolstikov in a speech at the meeting said that the DPRK has become a powerful socialist state and a beacon of socialism brightly indicating the road to be followed by the world progressive people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mohammad Aslam Nagi, secretary general of the Lahore Branch of the Pakistan-Korea Friendship Association, in his speech at the meeting referred to the fact that the President founded the DPRK and built it into an independent and sovereign state dynamically advancing by relying on its own strength, not depending upon foreign forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ramon Jimenez Lopez, president of the Mexican Committee for the Study of Kimilsungism, in the seminar on exploits performed by the President in nation-building stressed that Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, have steadfastly maintained independence while decisively frustrating the pressure, interference, threat of a war and provocative moves of foreign forces under the banner of the Juche idea and Songun for the past six decades after the foundation of the Republic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Harpal Brar, chairman of the Communist Party of Great Britain (Marxist-Leninist), Andy Brooks, general secretary of the Central Committee of the New Communist Party of Britain, and Dermot Hudson, chairman of the British Association for the Study of Songun Policy, in the round-table talks highly praised the President who made great contribution to the cause of independence and the cause of socialism of the popular masses and undying exploits of Kim Jong Il who opened up a turning phase for building a great prosperous powerful nation while foiling the imperialist allied forces' moves to stifle the DPRK with his unique Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Messages of greetings to Kim Jong Il were adopted at the functions in Russia and Pakistan.

